5323	                    // and the transactions were not pruned (pindexFirstMissing
5324	                    // is null), it is a potential candidate. The check
5325	                    // excludes pruned blocks, because if any blocks were
5326	                    // pruned between pindex and the current chain tip, pindex will
5327	                    // only temporarily be added to setBlockIndexCandidates,
5328	                    // before being moved to m_blocks_unlinked. This check
5329	                    // could be improved to verify that if all blocks between
5330	                    // the chain tip and pindex have data, pindex must be a
5331	                    // candidate.
5332	                    //
5333	                    // If pindex is the chain tip, it also is a potential
5334	                    // candidate.
5335	                    //
5336	                    // If the chainstate was loaded from a snapshot and pindex
